Sentencas: NdBaCo2O5+delta (NBCO) based double perovskite is an attractive cathode material with many advantages, yet its electrochemical performance still cannot meet the requirements.
Titulo: Significant Zirconium Substitution Effect on the Oxygen Reduction Activity of the Cathode Material NdBaCo2O5+δ for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: We first design and prepare Zr cation doping NdBaCo1.95Zr0.05O5+delta and systematically study the effects of Zr-doping on the oxygen kinetics, redox, and electrical properties of NdBaCo1.95Zr0.05O5+delta as cathode material for oxygen conduction SOFCs.
Titulo: Significant Zirconium Substitution Effect on the Oxygen Reduction Activity of the Cathode Material NdBaCo2O5+δ for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: NdBaCo1.95Zr0.05O5+delta show rapid oxygen bulk diffusion coefficients and surface exchange coefficients through zirconium cations doping, reaching 5.827 X 10(-5) cm(2).s(-1) and 2.878 X 10(-4) cm.s(-1), respectively, at 700 degrees C, enabling the improved performance of oxygen reduction, and the polarization impedance is as low as 0.024 Omega.cm(2).
Titulo: Significant Zirconium Substitution Effect on the Oxygen Reduction Activity of the Cathode Material NdBaCo2O5+δ for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
